    <title>#2: Database normalization</title>
    <description>&lt;p&gt;
I was reviewing the database tables for my own modifications and I came across a huge normalization problem. The primary key of the &#34;eqdkp_member&#34; is member_id. However, in &#34;eqdkp_raid_attendee&#34; and &#34;eqdkp_items&#34; you are using the the member_name NOT the member_id.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
This causes big problems in normalization and consistency in the database. You can never change the member_name at the moment because it will break the linkage to other tables. Since the member_id is a primary_key (hence unqie and auto-incrementing) is never changed it certainly should be the identifier (and foreign key) of the &#34;eqdkp_raid_attendee&#34; and &#34;eqdkp_items&#34; tables.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
As it stands, the only way to change someones name is to replace all the previous names in those two tables + change the name in the members table. Changing those two tables to use the member id will allow you to change only field in all the tables (member_name in eqdkp_items).
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Gorndax
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Mantis: 0000172
&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
