   <item>
    <link>http://eqdkp.com/cgi-bin/trac.cgi/ticket/59</link>
    <guid isPermaLink="true">http://eqdkp.com/cgi-bin/trac.cgi/ticket/59</guid>
    <title>#59: Change Adjustment Screen - Make it accept pasted lists instead of Control Clicking multiples</title>
    <description>&lt;p&gt;
ADJUSTMENT ENTRY SYSTEM ENHANCEMENT REQUEST
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
This is a request I have for the adjustment entry screen after using EQDKP 1.3.0 for about 2 months.  It would make my life so much easier for maintaining and completing the DKP for our raids.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
1)
Please change the adjustment entry screen so that we can paste lists of adjustment names like creating a raid does instead of using CONTROL CLICK to select multiple people.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
2) 
An even better way to help us maintain this information would be to have the pastable list box similar to the Raid Entry screen, but have a button to click which will transfer all the names of the intended adjustee listing to a row by row listing which I could then adjust all of the names and their adjustment reasons and values individually and separately.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
There would be another button to PROCESS the list of rows and automatically generate separate adjustment entries per person.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
There would need to be a few extra entry boxes to handle default values.
Default Description, Default Value that should be set before the user clicks the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Convert to lines&lt;/strong&gt; button transfering items from the multi-line paste box to separate rows.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Example
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Multi-line paste box for the Names:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Default Description:  Raid Adjustment
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Default Value:  0.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Names:             
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Bob
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Frank
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Nick
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Clicking &lt;strong&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Convert to lines&lt;/strong&gt; converts the list of people entered into separate lines to be saved to separate rows in the adjustments table.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Bob,Raid Adjustment,0.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Frank,Raid Adjustment,0.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Nick,Raid Adjustment,0.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
And now I can just go down the list and adjust the description or amount as desired for the certain people.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Bob,Raid Adjustment,3.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Frank,Raid Adjustment,0.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Nick,Raid Adjustment,0.50
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;PROCESSING INTO SEPARATE ADJUSTMENT DETAIL LINES&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Clicking &lt;strong&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; PROCESS&lt;/strong&gt;   would create INDIVIDUAL adjustments PER person not a GROUP adjustment with multiple people with all with the same value.  
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
You could also add this as an option in the EQ configure system, to use NEW or OLD style system to give the old timers flexibility to use old system.
&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
